    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Trace allows users to toggle which systems to examine, and verbosity sets the level. How do you see these being merged into one?\r\n\r\nI understand the problem that this can be complex for someone starting out with gRPC, but once it is understood, the granularity of configuration should allow quicker debugging.\r\n\r\nHow about this proposal. setting GRPC_VERBOSITY to `ALL` will have the same effect as setting GRPC_TRACE to `all` and GRPC_VERBOSITY to `DEBUG`. I.e. maximum log dumping. That way if we want logs from a user, they only have to set one env var."
  },
